If the method doesn&#39;t return anything then it probably modifies fields
of the class somehow.  You can therefore test the value of this changed
object. ie:

public class Foo
{
  int x;

  public Foo(int x)
  {
    this.x=x;
  }

  public int getX()
  {
    return x;
  }

  public void incrementX()
  { 
    x++;
  }
}

public class FooTest extends TestCase
{
  public void testIncrementX()
  {
    Foo foo=new Foo(5);
    foo.incrementX();
    assertEquals(6,foo.getX());
  }
}

